    Scope and Contents
Huston, army veteran, discusses his experiences in Vietnam: military service near Saigon, ambushes, traveling through mined areas, and the deaths of military personnel. He also discusses his efforts to improve circumstances for veterans: the Vietnam Veterans Leadership Program, the Illinois Vietnam Veterans Act, amd the government hiring of veterans. 1 tape, 90 mins., 13 pp. 
Interview by Gary L. Maple, 1988 
